cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.ETM 

This paper deals with the optimization of voltage control in power systems, which involves the use of mathematical algorithms and techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems. Additionally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with the fast decoupled load flow Jacobian matrix, which is a key component in power system analysis and could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of case studies to verify the proposed method, which could fall under cs.ETM (Emerging Technologies).
